Package com.cafean.client.ui.clipboard

Class ClipboardListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.client.ui.clipboard.ClipboardListener
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    IntegratorClipboardListener
    public abstract class ClipboardListener
extends java.lang.Object
    A listener for copy/paste events related to models of a particular plug-in. Most plug-ins do not require the use of this listener and are fully supported by the CAFEAN core copy/paste logic.

    Before implementing an extension of this listener, ensure that the existing core dependencies, shared component and reconnection logic is does not support the interdependencies required by the plug-in.

    See Also:
    ComponentCopier.addClipboardListener(com.cafean.client.ui.clipboard.ClipboardListener), AbstractComponent.getSharedComponents(), AbstractComponent.getComponentDependencies(java.util.List), GenericObject.reconnectIdentReferences(boolean, boolean), AbstractComponent.reconnectImage(java.util.Vector, java.util.Vector), AbstractComponent.rebuildConnections(java.util.Vector, java.util.Vector)

    • Method Detail

      • clear

        public void clear()
        Clears this listener's state between each use. Note that this method may be called before and after each operation an unspecified number of times and should not be used to maintain state information.

        Listener extensions that override this method should ensure that the base implementation is called.

      • copyModelCreated

        public void copyModelCreated​(AbstractModel sourceModel,
                             AbstractModel copyModel)
        Notifies the listener that a "Copy Model" (i.e. clipboard component container model) has been created that will be used to copy components from the given source model. This method is intended to be used by plug-ins to configure any model properties that may be necessary to ensure that the components being copied will be available to the ComponentPaster via AbstractModel.getComponents().
        Parameters:
        sourceModel - the AbstractModel from which the components will be copied
        copyModel - the AbstractModel to which the components will be copied on the clipboard to await future paste operations.

      • componentsCopying

        public void componentsCopying​(java.util.List sourceComps,
                              java.util.List destComps,
                              AbstractModel copyModel)
        Notifies this listener that the given source components have been collected and duplicated into destComps and will be inserted into the copy model.

        Note that sourceComps and destComps are parallel lists in identical order. Extensions of this class may modify these lists but must ensure that the resulting lists are the same size and in the same order.

        Parameters:
        sourceComps - a List containing the AbstractComponents in the source model that were duplicated into destComps.
        destComps - a List containing the duplicated AbstractComponents that will be inserted into the copy model.
        copyModel - the AbstractModel that the destination components will be inserted into.

      • componentsCopied

        public void componentsCopied​(java.util.List sourceComps,
                             java.util.List destComps,
                             AbstractModel copyModel)
        Notifies this listener that the given destination components have been inserted into the copy model.

        Note that modifications to sourceComps and destComps at this point will have no effect on the copy operation.

        Parameters:
        sourceComps - a List containing the AbstractComponents in the source model that were duplicated.
        destComps - a List containing the duplicated AbstractComponents that were inserted into the copy model.
        copyModel - the AbstractModel that the destination components were inserted into.

      • pasteBegun

        public void pasteBegun​(java.util.List sourceComps,
                       AbstractModel targetModel,
                       javax.swing.undo.CompoundEdit edit)
                throws PasteAbortedException
        Notifies this listener that the given components have been collected, (along with all component dependencies, shared components, etc.) and will be pasted into the target model.

        Note that the components have not been duplicated and no modifications of the target model have occurred at this point.

        Parameters:
        sourceComps - a List containing the AbstractComponents in the copy model that will be duplicated and inserted into the target model.
        targetModel - the AbstractModel that the components will be pasted into. (i.e. duplicated and inserted)
        edit - a CompoundEdit for use in undoing any operations performed by this listener.
        Throws:
        PasteAbortedException - if the paste should be aborted. If a message is included in this exception it will be displayed as a Message Mindow error message.
        See Also:
        AbstractComponent.getSharedComponents(), AbstractComponent.getComponentDependencies(java.util.List)

      • pasteInserted

        public void pasteInserted​(java.util.List sourceComps,
                          java.util.List destComps,
                          AbstractModel targetModel,
                          javax.swing.undo.CompoundEdit edit)
                   throws PasteAbortedException
        Notifies this listener that the given components have been pasted into the target model but have not been reconnected. Unresolved ident references and DB_IDs have not been cleared at this point.

        Note that sourceComps and destComps are parallel lists in identical order.

        Parameters:
        sourceComps - a List containing the AbstractComponents in the copy model that were duplicated and inserted into the target model.
        destComps - a List containing the pasted AbstractComponents in the target model corresponding to the components in sourceComps.
        targetModel - the AbstractModel that the components were pasted into
        edit - a CompoundEdit for use in undoing any follow-up operations performed by this listener.
        Throws:
        PasteAbortedException - if the paste should be aborted. If a message is included in this exception it will be displayed as a message window error message.

      • pasteCompleted

        public void pasteCompleted​(java.util.List sourceComps,
                           java.util.List destComps,
                           AbstractModel targetModel,
                           javax.swing.undo.CompoundEdit edit)
                    throws PasteAbortedException
        Notifies this listener that the given components have been pasted into the target model and reconnected successfully. Unresolved ident references and DB_IDs have been cleared at this point.

        Note that sourceComps and destComps are parallel lists in identical order.

        Parameters:
        sourceComps - a List containing the AbstractComponents in the copy model that were duplicated and inserted into the target model.
        destComps - a List containing the pasted AbstractComponents in the target model corresponding to the components in sourceComps.
        targetModel - the AbstractModel that the components were pasted into
        edit - a CompoundEdit for use in undoing any follow-up operations performed by this listener.
        Throws:
        PasteAbortedException - if the paste should be aborted. If a message is included in this exception it will be displayed as a message window error message.
        See Also:
        GenericObject.reconnectIdentReferences(boolean, boolean), AbstractComponent.reconnectImage(java.util.Vector, java.util.Vector), AbstractComponent.rebuildConnections(java.util.Vector, java.util.Vector)

      • showPasteSpecialDialog

        public boolean showPasteSpecialDialog​(AbstractModel sourceModel,
                                      DrawnView targetView,
                                      AbstractModel targetModel,
                                      boolean sameModel,
                                      ComponentPaster paster,
                                      javax.swing.undo.CompoundEdit edit)
        Directs this clipboard listener to show the paste special dialog.

        The default implementation shows the component number centric paste special dialog that allows the user to select the number of sets to be pasted and their component number offsets.

        This method may be overridden to replace the base paste special dialog (by not calling super) or may be called in addition (before or after) plug-in specific paste special dialog(s).

        Returns:
        false if the operation was cancelled by the user

      • isIntegratorSupported

        public boolean isIntegratorSupported()
        Returns false if this listener cannot be used by the SubsystemIntegrator. The default implementation returns true.
